        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "tlFXz",
          "name": "behavior",
          "fill": "#9A9BA5",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 480,
          "content": "Appears when a runner has unread mission mail and the nudge is parked behind pending terminal input (PendingInput). Floats over the pane below the tab strip — never in layout flow, so the PTY is not resized. The Clear input button emits a single Enter (↵) through the ordinary local-input write path — identical to pressing the key: a leftover draft is submitted rather than discarded, an empty box is a no-op. ClearPending fires organically and the 500ms grace + fire-time re-check still apply (typing during the grace re-parks delivery). The button is hidden while the runner is busy — Enter mid-turn could submit pending text into the active turn. Copy does not assert a draft exists — backspace-cleared input is undetectable. Clears when delivery proceeds, when unread reaches zero, on session exit, and on mission unmount; a workspace opened after the transition fired shows nothing until unread changes (no snapshot hydration).",
          "lineHeight": 1.5,
          "fontFamily": "Inter",
          "fontSize": 12,
          "fontWeight": "normal"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "fileToken": "a8d0e631-a307-4f94-a938-6f0ff78c69a7"
